PipePub Manual
==============

Complete command-line reference for PipePub


SYNOPSIS
--------

./tools/pipepub.sh [COMMAND] [OPTIONS]

<!-- quick-help -->

QUICK HELP
----------

./tools/pipepub.sh              - Interactive menu
./tools/pipepub.sh publish      - Publish articles
./tools/pipepub.sh secrets      - Manage secrets
./tools/pipepub.sh check        - Check system dependencies
./tools/pipepub.sh test         - Run test suite
./tools/pipepub.sh --help       - Show this help
./tools/pipepub.sh --man        - Show full manual
./tools/pipepub.sh --doc        - Open manual file
./tools/pipepub.sh --version    - Show version
./tools/pipepub.sh -v           - Same as --version

<!-- end-quick-help -->


COMMANDS
--------

publish
    Publish articles to configured platforms.

    Environment variables:
        MANUAL_FILENAMES    Space-separated list of files to publish
        DRY_RUN             Set to true for test mode (no API calls)
        LOG_LEVEL           Set to debug for verbose logging

    Interactive mode: If no arguments provided, prompts for file selection.

secrets
    Manage API tokens and credentials in OS keychain.

    Subcommands:
        add devto           Add Dev.to API token
        add hashnode        Add Hashnode token + publication ID
        add medium          Add Medium legacy token
        add github          Add GitHub token (gist scope)
        list                List configured services
        export              Export secrets as environment variables
        delete <service>    Remove service secrets

    Interactive mode: If no arguments provided, launches interactive menu.

check
    Verify system dependencies and configuration.

    Checks performed:
        - Dependencies: git, curl, jq, openssl
        - Keychain: OS keychain availability
        - Configuration: .env file presence and validity
        - Secrets: Which services have configured secrets

test
    Run the test suite.

    Options:
        --filter=NAME       Run only test file matching NAME
        --tag=TAG           Run only tests with TAG
        --exclude=TAG       Exclude tests with TAG
        --update-snapshots  Update snapshot files
        --debug             Enable debug logging

    Interactive mode: If no arguments provided, launches test selection menu.

help
    Display help documentation.
    Aliases: --help, -h

man
    Display this full manual.
    Aliases: --man, -m

doc
    Open documentation file in browser or default application.
    Aliases: --doc, -d

version
    Display version information.
    Aliases: --version, -v


ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
---------------------

Application Configuration:
    APP_NAME        PipePub                     Application display name
    APP_VERSION     v1.0.0                      Version shown in UI
    APP_ICON        ⮻

Logging Configuration:
    LOG_LEVEL       info                        debug, info, warning, error
    LOG_OUTPUT      console                     console, file, both
    LOG_QUIET       false                       Suppress all output
    LOG_NO_ICONS    false

Publisher Defaults:
    PUBLISHER_LANG  en-us                       Language/locale
    PUBLISHER_STATUS draft                      draft, public
    PUBLISHER_AUTO  true                        Auto-publish on push
    PUBLISHER_GIST  true                        Table-to-Gist conversion

Runtime Flags:
    DRY_RUN         false
    CI              (unset)
    DEBUG           false                       Enable verbose output


FILES
-----

.env                Local environment configuration
.env.example        Template for .env
posts/              User articles (markdown files)
docs/               Documentation
.tmp/               Temporary runtime files
.logs/              Pipeline execution logs
.reports/           Test reports (JSON)


EXIT CODES
----------

0   Success
1   General error
2   Missing dependency
3   Configuration error
4   Secret error
5   API error
6   Validation error


EXAMPLES
--------

Basic usage:

    ./tools/pipepub.sh
    ./tools/pipepub.sh publish
    ./tools/pipepub.sh secrets add devto
    ./tools/pipepub.sh check
    ./tools/pipepub.sh test

Advanced usage:

    DRY_RUN=true ./tools/pipepub.sh publish
    LOG_LEVEL=debug ./tools/pipepub.sh publish
    MANUAL_FILENAMES="article1.md article2.md" ./tools/pipepub.sh publish
    ./tools/pipepub.sh secrets export


